//Matthew Penner

Instructions:

(1) Compile the program using 'make'
(2) Run the program using ./a.out
(3) When prompted with numerical choices, type an integer that corresponds with one of the choices provided 
(it will not error if you type in the wrong int, it just automatically assumes no)
----->If you enter in an invalid option (like an incorrect type), the program will carry out exception handling
(4) When prompted to type in numerical values for properties of a pet you would like to add, type in an integer format
(5) Press 0 if you want to exit the program when prompted
